{{doc/start}}
Renders a styled infobox for an in-game building. Data is pulled automatically from [[Module:Data/Buildings]]. The infobox displays name, description, type, size, power consumption or generation, energy capacity, module slots, conveyor and pipe slots, recipe tags, and the upgrade path (e.g. Assembler I → Assembler II → Assembler III).

Pages using this template are auto-generated by <code>foundry_parser generate-pages</code>. Editors can add content below the infobox but should not modify the template call itself.

== Data source ==
Building data comes from [[Module:Data/Buildings]], which is auto-generated by running:
<pre>foundry_parser generate-lua</pre>
from the game installation at <code>F:\SteamLibrary\SteamApps\common\FOUNDRY</code>. Do not edit data modules directly.

== Usage ==
<pre>
{{Infobox Building|id=_base_assembler_i}}
{{Infobox Building|id=_base_assembler_i|image=Assembler I.png}}
</pre>

== Parameters ==
{| class="wikitable"
! Parameter !! Description !! Type !! Status
|-
| <code>id</code> || Building template identifier from the game data (e.g. <code>_base_assembler_i</code>). || String || Required
|-
| <code>image</code> || Image filename to display (e.g. <code>Assembler I.png</code>). The module prepends <code>Item_</code> automatically, so this looks up <code>File:Item_Assembler I.png</code>. || String || Optional
|}

== Notes ==
* Building size is rendered as X×Z×Y (width × depth × height) to match in-game display conventions.
* Power is shown as kW. Generation ranges (e.g. solar panels with min/max output) are displayed as a range.
* Upgrade paths are read from [[Module:Data/UpgradePaths]]; the current building is bolded and not linked.
* Buildings that connect to the walkway network show a "Connects to walkway" note.
* The infobox adds the building to <code>[[Category:Buildings]]</code> and <code>[[Category:TYPE buildings]]</code> automatically.
{{doc/end}}
